Problem Statement

A software company wants to develop a console-based Employee Record Management 
System to maintain employee information. As a Java developer, you are required 
to design the application using Normal Interface, Functional Interface,
Marker Interface (Serializable), and BufferedReader for accepting user input.

Develop the application based on the following requirements.


Requirements
Accept employee details using BufferedReader.
Create a Normal Interface to define employee-related operations.
Create a Functional Interface to calculate the employee bonus using a Lambda Expression.
Make the Employee class implement the Marker Interface (Serializable).
Serialize the employee object into a file and deserialize it to display the stored employee details.
Implement the application using a menu-driven program.Expected Output
